# Model & Rules

## Model (`model/`)

- `Board`: grid storage, bounds, cell get/set — no move-legality logic
- `Piece`: `{ kind, color }` value type — no virtual methods
- `Position`: grid coordinates — `isValid()` is necessary but not sufficient; always check board bounds
- `GameState`: selection, turn, game-over flags — engine-owned aggregate state

Model types must be usable without knowing about realtime, I/O, or rendering.

## Rules (`rules/`)

- Each piece implements `IPieceRule::legalDestinations(board, piece)`
- `RuleEngine::validateMove` composes: bounds → source nonempty → not friendly dest → piece rule
- Return `MoveValidation` with machine-readable `reason` strings in English

```cpp
struct MoveValidation {
    bool is_valid;
    std::string reason; // "ok" | "outside_board" | "empty_source" | ...
};
```

## Extending piece behavior

1. Add a new class implementing `IPieceRule`
2. Register it in `ruleFor(char kind)` factory
3. Add focused unit test under `tests/MoveRules*Test.cpp`
4. Do not add piece-specific branches inside `RuleEngine`
